modules.description: This module implements a vector data structure with support for operational transformation, enabling efficient merging of concurrent edits. It provides atomic operations like insertion, deletion, and element updates, along with patch generation and application using the Wagner-Fischer algorithm. Use cases include collaborative text editing and real-time document synchronization where conflict resolution is managed through a user-defined merge function.

This module implements a mergeable string vector with support for operational transformation. It provides atomic operations like `get`, `set`, `insert`, and `delete`, along with functions to compute and apply patches between strings, enabling conflict-free synchronization. It is suitable for collaborative text editing where concurrent changes must be merged reliably.

Implements a vector data structure with operational transformation for merging concurrent edits. Supports atomic insertions, deletions, and updates, along with patch generation and application using Wagner-Fischer. Designed for collaborative text editing and real-time document synchronization with user-defined conflict resolution.
